How to build and run.

Clone the repo:
git clone https://github.com/gvrose8192/SimpleDrive.git

From the ros2_ws directory build it:
colcon build --packages-select simple_drive

Keep in mind that all of these commands must be run from the ros2_ws workspace after source install/setup.[bash][zsh][other]

In a terminal Run it:
# ros2 run simple_drive simple_drive_node

The robot will enter the WAIT state.

In a second terminal run the service:

# ros2 run simple_drive reset_service_node

In a third terminal run the following command to start the robot movement sequence:

# ros2 service call /simple_drive/start std_srvs/srv/Trigger

After running it's movement sequence the robot will enter the DONE state.

Run the reset sequence to move back to the WAIT state.

#ros2 service call /simple_drive/reset std_srvs/srv/Trigger

The robot will enter the WAIT state again.

Run the start sequence to repeat the previous steps.

# ros2 service call /simple_drive/start std_srvs/srv/Trigger

The robot will execute the original sequence again.
